# Fluff Date: 2026-02-19 16:29:24
overview:<p>The Stalking Spider emerged in 3059 when Clan Cloud Cobra scientists acquired the remains of an Inner Sphere Tarantula and decided to use the captured 'Mech as the basis for their own quadrupedal design. Though four-legged BattleMechs had proven sturdier and more maneuverable than any two-legged 'Mech, pilot prejudice guaranteed they were never widely produced, even in the Clan Homeworlds where apparently successful designs like the Fire Scorpion and Thunder Stallion already existed. The Cloud Cobra scientists' greatest achievement was convincing Loremaster Eleni Riaz to push the new design into production at the Constantin Assembly Plant M27A-E on Homer.</p><p>At fifty tons, the Stalking Spider doubled the Tarantula's mass while retaining the quad layout and jump capability that defined its ancestor, creating a medium 'Mech that combined Clan-grade weapons technology with the inherent stability advantages of a quadrupedal chassis.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Stalking Spider's greatest asset is its stability. Clan Cloud Cobra tactical doctrine teams a BattleMech Trinary with several aerospace fighter Binaries or Trinaries to form Fang Clusters, and these forces often perform combat drops where the Stalking Spider's built-in jump jets and quadrupedal frame make it far better suited for absorbing the shocks and stresses of such operations than conventional bipedal designs.</p><p>The 'Mech's armament centers on a Type DDS "Kingston" extended-range PPC for long-range engagement, complemented by a pair of CCWP-14 SRM-4 launchers and two Series PPS-XIX medium pulse lasers for close-range work. Protected by eight tons of Compound RSH5 ferro-fibrous armor and driven by a standard 250-rated fusion engine, the Stalking Spider achieves a respectable 86 km/h, boosted to 119 km/h in short bursts by its MASC system. While alpha strikes can generate significant heat, an experienced pilot can manage the Stalking Spider's thermal output by alternating between long-range sniping with the PPC and closing to finish opponents with its pulse lasers and missiles.</p><p>The choice to mount the jump jets in the legs produces a distinctive side effect: during a jump, the pilot constantly adjusts trajectory by moving the 'Mech's legs, creating the impression that the 'Mech is crawling through the air. Combined with the Stalking Spider's already unnerving appearance, this effect can unsettle opposing commanders unfamiliar with the design.</p>

deployment:<p>Modified during the Jihad around 3072, the Stalking Spider 3 emphasizes close-range striking power and extreme mobility. The most dramatic change is the installation of eight improved jump jets, granting a remarkable 240-meter jump capability that allows the design to stalk opponents from above. The heavier weapons are replaced by an SRM-6 launcher and a pair of heavy small lasers, while the medium pulse lasers and a targeting computer are retained for accuracy. Additional armor enhances survivability in the close engagements this variant is designed to seek out. First confirmed among Jade Falcon forces captured during the Harvest Trials, the origin of this modification remains uncertain.</p>

history:<p>The first Stalking Spiders were delivered to the Clan Cloud Cobra military in March of 3059. In contrast to standard Clan procedure, a majority of these 'Mechs were distributed directly to front-line Clusters rather than held in reserve, including the four Delta Galaxy Clusters and both the 121st and 214th Cobra Fangs. This aggressive deployment pattern reflected the Cloud Cobras' confidence in the design and their eagerness to validate it in combat.</p><p>Unconfirmed rumors placed single Stalking Spiders among Clan Blood Spirit's Omega Galaxy and Clan Jade Falcon's Sigma Galaxy shortly after the design's introduction. Given how recently the 'Mech had been developed, intelligence analysts initially considered these reports unreliable. However, the Stalking Spider 3 variant was later confirmed among Jade Falcon forces captured during the Harvest Trials, with a holovid recording of a public Trial of Possession on Graus documenting the modified design. Whether this represented Cloud Cobra exports, Falcon engineering, or a Homeworld trade arrangement remained unclear.</p><p>The Stalking Spider's production at the Constantin Assembly Plant M27A-E on Homer continued under Clan Cloud Cobra ownership from the design's introduction through the early Dark Age era. The base model and the Stalking Spider 2 entered active production during the Civil War period, with both variants remaining in service through the Jihad. The Stalking Spider 3, introduced during the Jihad in 3072, represented the last known factory variant. By the late Dark Age, the factory's status became uncertain, with records listing ownership as unconfirmed Clan control, and active production data was no longer available.</p><p>The design's legacy extended beyond Cloud Cobra service when Clan Sea Fox, recognizing a commercial opportunity, acquired the Stalking Spider concept and redesigned it as the Stalking Spider II for sale to Inner Sphere markets beginning in 3110. This merchant Clan adaptation brought the quad 'Mech lineage that began with the Inner Sphere Tarantula full circle, with Clan-manufactured descendants of the original design being sold back to the very market that had inspired them.</p>

